attributes.value: / A X.509 v3 ([RFC5280]) parser, implemented with the [nom](https://github.com/Geal/nom)
/ It is written in pure Rust, fast, and makes extensive use of zero-copy. A lot of care is taken
/ to ensure security and safety of this crate, including design (recursion limit, defensive
/ programming), tests, and fuzzing. It also aims to be panic-free.
/ and is part of the [Rusticata](https://github.com/rusticata) project.
/ The main parsing method is [`parse_x509_der`](fn.parse_x509_der.html), which takes a
/ DER-encoded certificate as input, and builds a
/ For PEM-encoded certificates, use the [`pem`](pem/index.html) module.
/ Parsing a certificate in DER format:
/ - The `verify` feature adds support for (cryptographic) signature verification, based on ring.
/ /// Cryptographic signature verification: returns true if certificate was signed by issuer

defs.name: X509Error
defs.value:
pub enum X509Error {

    #[error("invalid X.509 name")]
    InvalidX509Name,

    #[error("invalid date")]
    InvalidDate,

    #[error("signature verification error")]
    SignatureVerificationError,

    #[error("signature unsupported algorithm")]
    SignatureUnsupportedAlgorithm,

    #[error("BER error: {0}")]
    Der(
        #[from]
        BerError),

    #[error("nom error: {0:?}")]
    NomError(ErrorKind),
}

pub enum PEMError {

    #[error("base64 decode error")]
    Base64DecodeError,

    #[error("incomplete PEM")]
    IncompletePEM,

    #[error("invalid header")]
    InvalidHeader,

    #[error("missing header")]
    MissingHeader,

    #[error("IO error: {0}")]
    IOError(
            #[from]
            std::io::Error),
}
